snippet: The current office was formed when the Verkhovna Rada of the Ukrainian Soviet Socialist Republic passed a law on 5 July 1991 establishing the office of the "President of the Ukrainian Soviet Socialist Republic."

title: Ukraine’s Presidents, Power Elites, and the Country’s Evolution | Wilson Center
snippet: As president, Leonid Kravchuk (1991–94) is remembered as the founder of independent Ukraine, and signer of the 1994 Budapest Memorandum on Security Assurances that renounced Ukraine’s nuclear status.

title: List of Presidents of Ukraine (1991 - 2022)
snippet: Its capital is Kyiv (Kiev) which is located on the Dnieper River in north-central Ukraine. In July 1991, the Verkhovna Rada of the Ukrainian Soviet Socialist Republic passed a law and the modern Ukrainian presidency was formed.

snippet: In February 2014 the government of Ukrainian Pres. Viktor Yanukovych was toppled after months of popular protests, and that May billionaire Petro Poroshenko was elected president of Ukraine.
